research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0068.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 67 was rejected before execution, so the mainline still has only the archived clean baseline at `two_stage_residual` `K=128` `EF=12` `signum` `LR=2.0e-3`. The highest-value next single question remains the first within-family learning-rate probe: does a modest upward shift to `LR=2.4e-3` improve early and mid-course descent for `two_stage_residual` without destabilizing the curve, relative to the archived `2.0e-3` baseline.","summary":"Run a single learning-rate probe within the `two_stage_residual` mainline by keeping `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, and changing only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"mainline_improvement","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the current mainline family and changes exactly one primary variable, which matches the Round 68 policy. Because the downward LR probe never actually ran, a modest upward LR test is the cleanest first recipe move from the confirmed baseline and directly checks whether the staged residual model is slightly under-driven at `2.0e-3`.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 68 resumes mainline tuning after a policy-rejected Round 67, so the only valid executed baseline remains `two_stage_residual` at `LR=2.0e-3` with `signum`.","This round is the first executed LR probe for `two_stage_residual`; judge it by full curve shape against the archived baseline, especially whether higher LR improves descent without adding instability.","If `2.4e-3` is unstable or worse, the next LR move should go downward from the archived baseline rather than exploring optimizer yet."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=2.4e-3` improves endpoint or overall curve shape versus `2.0e-3`, archive it as the new `two_stage_residual` mainline recipe.","If `LR=2.4e-3` is clearly worse or unstable, revert to the archived `2.0e-3` baseline and test `1.6e-3` next.","If `LR=2.4e-3` is mixed, use one more LR probe before considering an optimizer change."],"primary_variable":"learning_rate"}
